 access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAesthetics. 0aVulnerability (Personality trait) in art. 4aAbhängigkeit. 4aBildung. 4aBildungssoziologie. 4aBildungstheorie. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDifferenz. 4aErziehung. 4aInklusion. 4aIntersektionalität. 4aKulturelle Bildung. 4aKunst. 4aKunsttheorie. 4aKörper. 4aPostcolonial Studies. 4aPädagogik. 4aRassismus. 4aSorgearbeit. 4aSubjekt. 4aÄsthetik. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aArt.  aBody.  aCultural Education.  aCultural Studies.  aDifference.  aEducation.  aInclusion.  aIntersectionality.  aPedagogy.  aPostcolonial Studies.  aRacism.  aSociology of Education.  aSubject.  aTheory of Art.  aTheory of Education.1 aAktas, Ulas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAktaş, Ulaş, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBering, Kunibert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBilstein, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoger, Mai-Anh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastro Varela, María do Mar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDederich, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer-Drawe, Käte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaimondi, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZirfas, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dD